Report: act_report¶

INSIGHTS¶

In the data wrangling project carried out, Insights were gotten from analyzing the already cleaned data. A few questions were posed, to which the dataset was analysed using various pandas functions and libraries to gain insights on the data. The questions posed are:

1.what is the most popular dog breed

I carried out this analysis using the value_counts function. value_counts function was used to get the needed insight from the dataset. After the value_counts function was used on the dog_breed column,the golden retriever breed was discovered to be the most popular dog breed in the dataset.

2.Top 5 dog breed based on favorite count

This was carried out using the groupby function. the dog_breed column was grouped based on favorite_count, with the numpy library used to filter out the top 5 dog breeds. These breeds were then sorted in ascending order to arrange them from smallest to largest number. The golden retriever was found to have the highest number, with labrador_retriever,pembroke,chihuahua and french_bulldog coming in descending order on the list.

  1. what are the most common dog names?

For this, the groupby function was also used. I grouped the names column and also deployed the count function to ascertain the number of times a certain name was found in the column. After analysis;charlie,cooper and oliver, were revealed to be the most common names of dogs.

VISUALIZATION¶

For this, first, the master dataset was queried to filter out data on dog_breed column with golden retrievers. This filtered data was sorted in descending order on favorite_count and the golden retriever named zoey was the top golden retriever. The requests,io and PIL libraries were used to visualize the top golden retriever based on favorite count count.
